<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species had been placed in the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Copepoda" family="Caligidae" genus="Pseudocaligus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudocaligus" order="Poecilostomatoida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pseudocaligus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is now synonymized with 
<taxonomicName class="Hexanauplia" family="Caligidae" genus="Caligus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Caligus" order="Caligoida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Caligus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
through a molecular analysis (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1186/1756-3305-6-336" author="Freeman, MA" journalOrPublisher="Parasites &amp; Vectors" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 9" refId="B14" refString="Freeman, MA, Anshary, H, Ogawa, K, 2013. Multiple gene analyses of caligid copepods indicate that the reduction of a thoracic appendage in Pseudocaligus represents convergent evolution. Parasites &amp; Vectors 6 (1): 1 - 9, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1186/1756-3305-6-336" title="Multiple gene analyses of caligid copepods indicate that the reduction of a thoracic appendage in Pseudocaligus represents convergent evolution." url="https://doi.org/10.1186/1756-3305-6-336" volume="6" year="2013">Freeman et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yamaguti" authorityYear="1936" class="Hexanauplia" family="Caligidae" genus="Caligus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Caligus fugu" order="Caligoida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fugu">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Caligus fugu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is frequently found on the puffer fish 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jordan &amp; Snyder" baseAuthorityYear="1901" class="Actinopterygii" family="Tetraodontidae" genus="Takifugu" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Takifugu niphobles" order="Tetraodontiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="niphobles">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Takifugu niphobles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Jordan &amp; Snyder, 1901).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
